message.content:
cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper presents a new shape analysis technique for reasoning about data structures in programs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper focuses on developing an automated analysis technique for verifying properties of data structures in software programs. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses graph grammars to represent both the concrete and abstract domains of the data structures, which can be seen as a logical approach to shape analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper applies the proposed analysis technique to various programs manipulating AVL trees, doubly-linked lists, and combinations of both, which are classic data structures. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper extends context-free graph grammars to model complex data structures, which can be seen as a contribution to the theory of formal languages and automata.
